reviewText: Volume three contains a number of great episodes, and was the least-produced (and therefore hardest to locate) of the five DVD sets of Garfield & Friends.  If you can get your hands on a copy of this set, grab it quickly- it has not yet been released in digital format, and PAWS is not exactly being speedy about the release date.  Pat Buttram (the Sheriff of Nottingham in Disney's "Robin Hood") provides guest voicing, as does Paul Winchell of "Tigger" fame (ironically, Mr. Winchell provided the voices of both the good guy and the bad guy in the "Supermarket Mania", in a partial head-nod to his polar opposite roles of Winnie the Pooh's "Tigger" and The Smurfs' "Gargamel"). As usual, the mix of these cartoons include everyone's least favorite beings, the Buddy Bears, as well as Jim Davis' spoof on the early Warner Bros "three bears" of Goldi...er...Odielocks fame.

reviewText: Garfield and Friends continue off from where they left off from volume 2.  Garfield and Friends does a fantastic job of inserting humor for both the young and older audiences.Volume 3 starts also episodes that are not shown in reruns nearly as much as volume 1 or 2.  I hadn't seen a few of the episodes on volume 3, which was quite a pleasant surprise.  Overall this is another great volume of Garfield and Friends episodes.  Quality is really good and sound is equally impressive.  Continue your Garfield and Friends collection or just start to see the lesser known episodes with this volume 3 DVD set.
summary: Saturday mornings need a return of Garfied and Friends

reviewText: Volume three of Garfield and Friends is here continuing a great Fox effort at bringing out the entire run of the classic cartoon.  You get 24 episodes of the TV show over 3 discs which includes some 70 tunes or so...if I counted right.  This season was 1990 to 1991 and included some fantastic Garfield tunes as well as tunes from the rest of the cast such as Orson Pig, Wade Duck and all the rest.Just a few of the classic episodes include:"Count lasagna" in a story Jon writes, Garfield is Count lasagna who steals italian food from delivery guys."For Cats Only" Garfield hosts a TV show for cats only explaining their plan of infiltrating humanity and having humans wait on them hand and foot.  Hilarious!"Hare Replacement" Jon is doing a magic act and his rabbit escapes, forcing Jon to put Garfield in a bunny suit as a replacement."Moo Cow Mutt" Garfield convinces Odie he is really a cow and Odie starts acting like one but Jon turns the tables on Garfield."Squeak Previews" a Parody of the old Siskel and Ebert movie review show with two mice playing the part of the reviwers."Annoying Things"  Garfield is warned by a dog not to say anything bad about dogs during his show.  Nermal causes Garfield to mess up when he holds up a cue card saying dogs are annoying."The idol of Id"  Jon, Odie, and Garfield visit a museum.  When Garfield and Odie touch the same idol, their minds switch bodies!Wow!  How can you go wrong?  Over eight hours of classic Garfield toons! Thank you fox for another great and great looking set. Oh..and there are trailers for the Garfield movie too!

reviewText: Finally got Garfield & Friends Vol-3!  Unfortunately I am stuck at work so won't get to start watching em till tomorrow.  I don't think there was a better Cartoon Series.  That was the only thing I looked forward to Saturday when I was younger.  This will have episodes 49-72.  We will still be expecting Vol 4 and 5 to complete all 121 episodes, but I have found no word on a timeframe.My favorites on here are US Acres 'Over The Rainbow' with voice of Rod Roddy (price is right) announcing what is won for the Dirty Sock in the 'end of the rainbow' game. Garfield 'Jukebox Jon' where Jon has an interview to get a job and the boss states Jon is level-Headed and not a wierdo, then which Jon walks in speaking spanish and making funny sounds!  Also 'Rodent Rampage', which has one of the best 'songs' from the Garfield toons, where Jon breaks into a song when he spots a mouse in the Kitchen "Garfield there's a mouse in the house"  "Let Me Sleep!"Another note, the next (and maybe final) Garfield 'Specials' DVD is also available for pre-order now, Called 'Garfield Fantasies'.
